<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="75" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="75">
<taxonomicName LSID="03E51954-2442-5FD5-AC3A-723AB3AB38C0" authority="(Bezzi, 1913)" baseAuthorityName="Bezzi" baseAuthorityYear="1913" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" genus="Campiglossa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Campiglossa lyncea" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="75" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lyncea">Campiglossa lyncea (Bezzi, 1913)</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="75" type="reference_group">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="75">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bezzi" authorityYear="1913" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" genus="Tephritis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Tephritis lyncea" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="75" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lyncea">Tephritis lyncea</taxonomicName>
Bezzi, 1913: 165. Type locality: Darjeeling, E. Himalayas, West Bengal, India.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="75" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="75">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="75">
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Bezzi" baseAuthorityYear="1913" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" genus="Campiglossa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Campiglossa lyncea" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="75" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lyncea">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">Campiglossa lyncea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distinguished from other Indian species by its mostly black femora, white posterior notopleural seta, two hyaline marginal spots in cell r2+3, and large, often coalesced, hyaline discal spots. This species is known only from northern India and includes the record of 
<taxonomicName genus="C." lsidName="C. absinthii" pageId="0" pageNumber="75" rank="species" species="absinthii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">C. absinthii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Fabricius, 1805 from Solan, Himachal Pradesh (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1080/00305316.2005.10417450" author="Agarwal, ML" journalOrPublisher="Oriental Insects" pageId="0" pageNumber="75" pagination="371 - 433" refId="B2" refString="Agarwal, ML, Sueyoshi, M, 2005. Catalogue of Indian fruit flies (Diptera: Tephritidae). Oriental Insects 39: 371 - 433, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1080/00305316.2005.10417450" title="Catalogue of Indian fruit flies (Diptera: Tephritidae)." url="https://doi.org/10.1080/00305316.2005.10417450" volume="39" year="2005">Agarwal and Sueyoshi 2005</bibRefCitation>
), which was misidentified as the synonym 
<taxonomicName genus="C." lsidName="C. parvula" pageId="0" pageNumber="75" rank="species" species="parvula">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">C. parvula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Loew, 1862) by 
<bibRefCitation author="Kapoor, VC" journalOrPublisher="Journal of the Natural History Museum, Nepal" pageId="0" pageNumber="75" pagination="147 - 149" refId="B14" refString="Kapoor, VC, Agarwal, ML, Grewel, JS, 1979a. Three new records of fruit flies from India with a note on wing venation of Sphenella sinensis (Dipt.: Teph.). Journal of the Natural History Museum, Nepal 3 (4): 147 - 149" title="Three new records of fruit flies from India with a note on wing venation of Sphenella sinensis (Dipt.: Teph.)." volume="3" year="1979 a">Kapoor et al. (1979a)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Kapoor, VC" journalOrPublisher="Invertebrate Taxonomy" pageId="0" pageNumber="75" refId="B13" refString="Kapoor, VC, 1993. Indian Fruit Flies (Insecta: Diptera: Tephritidae). International Science Publisher, New York, viii + 228 pp." title="Indian Fruit Flies (Insecta: Diptera: Tephritidae). International Science Publisher, New York, viii + 228 pp." year="1993">Kapoor (1993)</bibRefCitation>
. The illustration of 
<taxonomicName genus="C." lsidName="C. parvula" pageId="0" pageNumber="75" rank="species" species="parvula">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">C. parvula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Kapoor, VC" journalOrPublisher="Invertebrate Taxonomy" pageId="0" pageNumber="75" refId="B13" refString="Kapoor, VC, 1993. Indian Fruit Flies (Insecta: Diptera: Tephritidae). International Science Publisher, New York, viii + 228 pp." title="Indian Fruit Flies (Insecta: Diptera: Tephritidae). International Science Publisher, New York, viii + 228 pp." year="1993">Kapoor (1993)</bibRefCitation>
closely matches 
<taxonomicName genus="C." lsidName="C. lyncea" pageId="0" pageNumber="75" rank="species" species="lyncea">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">C. lyncea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
of 
<bibRefCitation author="Bezzi, M" journalOrPublisher="Memoirs of the Indian Museum" pageId="0" pageNumber="75" pagination="53 - 175" refId="B4" refString="Bezzi, M, 1913. Indian trypaneids (fruit-flies) in the collection of the Indian Museum, Calcutta. Memoirs of the Indian Museum 3: 53 - 175" title="Indian trypaneids (fruit-flies) in the collection of the Indian Museum, Calcutta." volume="3" year="1913">Bezzi (1913)</bibRefCitation>
, whereas the figure of 
<taxonomicName genus="C." lsidName="C. lyncea" pageId="0" pageNumber="75" rank="species" species="lyncea">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">C. lyncea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<bibRefCitation author="Kapoor, VC" journalOrPublisher="Invertebrate Taxonomy" pageId="0" pageNumber="75" refId="B13" refString="Kapoor, VC, 1993. Indian Fruit Flies (Insecta: Diptera: Tephritidae). International Science Publisher, New York, viii + 228 pp." title="Indian Fruit Flies (Insecta: Diptera: Tephritidae). International Science Publisher, New York, viii + 228 pp." year="1993">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Kapoor’s">Kapoor's</normalizedToken>
(1993)
</bibRefCitation>
publication is copied from 
<bibRefCitation author="Hardy, DE" journalOrPublisher="Steenstrupia" pageId="0" pageNumber="75" refId="B10" refString="Hardy, DE, 1973. The fruit flies (Tephritidae-Diptera) of Thailand and bordering countries. Pacific Insects Monograph 31: 1-353, pls 1-8." title="The fruit flies (Tephritidae-Diptera) of Thailand and bordering countries. Pacific Insects Monograph 31: 1 - 353, pls 1 - 8." year="1973">Hardy (1973)</bibRefCitation>
and is neither this species nor Indian. Hence, 
<bibRefCitation author="Hardy, DE" journalOrPublisher="Steenstrupia" pageId="0" pageNumber="75" refId="B10" refString="Hardy, DE, 1973. The fruit flies (Tephritidae-Diptera) of Thailand and bordering countries. Pacific Insects Monograph 31: 1-353, pls 1-8." title="The fruit flies (Tephritidae-Diptera) of Thailand and bordering countries. Pacific Insects Monograph 31: 1 - 353, pls 1 - 8." year="1973">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Hardy’s">Hardy's</normalizedToken>
(1973)
</bibRefCitation>
Vietnamese records, considered to be conspecific with 
<bibRefCitation author="Kapoor, VC" journalOrPublisher="Invertebrate Taxonomy" pageId="0" pageNumber="75" refId="B13" refString="Kapoor, VC, 1993. Indian Fruit Flies (Insecta: Diptera: Tephritidae). International Science Publisher, New York, viii + 228 pp." title="Indian Fruit Flies (Insecta: Diptera: Tephritidae). International Science Publisher, New York, viii + 228 pp." year="1993">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Kapoor’s">Kapoor's</normalizedToken>
(1993)
</bibRefCitation>
figure of ' 
<taxonomicName genus="C." lsidName="C. lyncea" pageId="0" pageNumber="75" rank="species" species="lyncea">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">C. lyncea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
' by 
<bibRefCitation author="Hancock, DL" journalOrPublisher="Australian Entomologist" pageId="0" pageNumber="75" pagination="77 - 72" refId="B8" refString="Hancock, DL, 2008. Systematic notes on some species in the fruit fly Tribe Tephritini (Diptera: Tephritidae: Tephritinae) in the Asian and Pacific Regions. Australian Entomologist 35 (2): 77 - 72" title="Systematic notes on some species in the fruit fly Tribe Tephritini (Diptera: Tephritidae: Tephritinae) in the Asian and Pacific Regions." volume="35" year="2008">Hancock (2008)</bibRefCitation>
, are also excluded. The syntypes of 
<taxonomicName genus="C." lsidName="C. lyncea" pageId="0" pageNumber="75" rank="species" species="lyncea">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">C. lyncea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, deposited in ZSI, are damaged (Banerjee, D; 
<taxonomicName genus="C." lsidName="" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="75" rank="order">Diptera</taxonomicName>
Section, ZSI, pers. comm.) and were not available on loan. Hence, a detailed diagnosis and redescription are not included.
</paragraph>
